4. conciliabula: the conciliabu- lum was in Italy the name of a class of villages inferior to the civitates (municipia and coloniae) ; the word may here be used in general for vil- lages, but is probably used, as ety- mologically it may be, to indicate public gutherings. In either case it designates assemblies regularly convened or of a public character, while coetus are irregular gatherings called for some special purpose.
